@jakovanrensburg  @lylenutt 

We do not store XML activity for every login. On Login, the service changes the Session Token, Hash and Salt which means that a XML Activity of yesterday compared to an XML Activity of today will automatically have differences in Session Token, Hash and Salt as the service changes these values daily (with no XML Activity being stored).

With the service changing these values all the time we wont be able to tell when a user changed their password. Unless we cater for it separately on the reset password sproc.
